Estimated reading time: 6 minutes

By Liu Chen

I'm one of five million people who have left China and returned home. I never thought that a Spring Festival could be so difficult. Every day feels like a year.

I always take out my phone in the hope of seeing good news, but I can't help but cry, feel dizzy, Tinnitus and palpitations. I know I can't do this, except report my health every day, try not to use my phone, sometimes can't control to open twitter, and then shut it down before the information is loaded.

I didn't think it would come to this before I went home.

I boarded the train home on January 21st. Before this, the end of the year is not busy finishing work, day by day forward. The virus spread silently, and the people who lived in the city, including me, still had no idea. Subway, bus shuttle in the city, come and go as before.

One after another, the network on the news of new pneumonia more and more, unable to distinguish true and false. I had to rely on my limited experience and pick up a few official news releases and academic sources as a reliable source.

I'm upset. There's still too little information. But I did not fully pay attention to this time, always feel this virus is far away from me, so young will not be infected. I started wearing a mask to work and never dared to go to the market again. Living off what he had saved, The Art of Soloing didn't eat much.

In this way, slowly, more and more information, it is difficult to distinguish true and false. Day By day, I'm on my way home.

January 21,5:00 a.m. , sleet in Wuhan. I took a taxi to Wuhan Station. The driver was wearing a mask. We had no communication the whole time.

Crossing the river soon arrived at Wuhan Station, I mixed feelings, in front of the station took a photo. The ticket counters were full of people wearing masks, and I made it through a series of checks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Passengers wearing face masks prepare to check their tickets at Wuhan Railway Station in Hubei Province on Jan. 21. Photo by Zheng Li, reporter of Zhongqingbao Zhongqingnet

I got on the train to go home. Soon after I left Wuhan, I saw a patch of snow outside my window. I used to look forward to this time, this time began to regret going home, constantly wondering whether they will carry the virus, will go home will harm the family. I can't take off my mask. I can't go to the bathroom.

Back home, I began a 14-day home quarantine. Because, the city notice to take the initiative to go to the hospital for examination, but I called to consult, the Designated Hospital Limited reagent box is not enough to give me such a non-febrile person to use, can only first hold the suspected case, the person on the other end of the phone advised me to quarantine at home.

The village has issued a notice to collect information about people returning from Wuhan. I filled it out and turned it in, and the next day the hospital sent a car to the house to take my temperature. The third day (January 23) , Wuhan "closed the city. ".

I can't tell you what it's like to wake up to this.

In Wuhan four years of university, after graduation in my current unit to participate in the work so far, this is my fifth year in Wuhan. My teachers, classmates and colleagues were all there. Usually mouth said Wuhan this is not good that to change, to this time only worry. What are they gonNA do with the people that are still in the city.

The news from the group was ringing off the hook. My friends and I were worried about whether we were Virus latency, taking our temperature, and taking our medicine. I was afraid that I was a carrier of the virus, disinfection home quarantine step by step, my family and I never went out together.

In the three days leading up to New Year's Eve, I had been collecting information about the outbreak on the Internet every day, getting more and more confirmed cases and feeling more and more uneasy.

There were eight people in our town who had come back from Wuhan, and I was one of the main ones to watch. After the personal information report, the town secretary personally to my home, the hospital sent a car to the doctor home for me to take a temperature check, the town police station, District Public Security Bureau, epidemic prevention departments to investigate and advise. I know I have to cooperate with the work, but a little aggrieved, I am not a virus, nor a time bomb, I just go home for the New Year, who would have thought to encounter such a situation.

The staff worked very hard, and their epidemic prevention work was well done. New Year's Day this day is basically calm down, my heart is no longer so panic.

During the home quarantine, a special cordon was set up in front of my house. Every day the doctor had a routine check-up, and I waited for him at home every day. The big brother of that doctor comforted me and said: "Soon, February 3 will be over, when you are happy to come to me to play. "

This is a battle, not only Wuhan, I know that all over the country at this moment are fighting the epidemic.

Friends and relatives of the news received one after another, I can only tell them do not go out, until the storm has passed to meet again. I don't know if I'm listening. My mother was in her 80s and couldn't hear because her ears weren't working. New Year's day we did not go to her New Year's Day, the fourth day she has been crying, but we can do ah, only video has been loudly told that she can go to see her in a week. But she can't hear anything. I know she's scared.

In the real world, the network world, the human sentiment cold warm all appears in the epidemic situation to be clear-cut. The Lunar New Year, which was supposed to be a family reunion, was overshadowed by the spread of the epidemic. I think, this is probably my most reluctant one winter vacation, I want to return to Wuhan earlier.

Perhaps after should do something, life health education can apply for inclusion in the curriculum of our education, from a young age, always can not be wrong, more than one person in the family understand is always good.

Seeing a teacher in a friend's circle, he said, the virus is our discipline, home observation, isolation or prevention is to attend a full-time training class, just do not know what the next lesson.

In the days when we are at home, there are probably many people like me who have experienced all kinds of psychological states, such as panic, irritability, fluke, etc. . Perhaps it would be more comfortable to find something to do for yourself. Read a book, Cook a new dish, exercise can be, out of the Social Day to calm down, do not fall into another kind of chaos.

Finally, as I wrote in the circle of friends that sentence: Waiting for the clouds to open fog scattered in the spring.
